I am working on creating an optimized workflow.
I am going to write lessons as markdown files. 
Then I will put into markdown to a html converter.
This will convert into just a main section that I will manually insert into modular templates across all subjects. 


I have a skeleton for html files.
It is modular for loading html elements using javascript.
My plan:



1. Modular template for html files. Consistent look across all pages.
2. Use javascript loaders to load html.
3. Use external stylesheet to instantly maintain all pages.
4. Write lesson in markdown and then convert to html. Insert converted html into skeleton for each new page.
5. Keep seperate files for each section of the template to be loaded: hero, header, navbar, footer, etc.



I already have the markdown converter.
I still am locking down the style of the webpages.
I can get the color palette and typography I want with css but the navbar is difficult.
On desktop I would like a visible navbar with links inline.
On moblie I would like links to collapse.
On mobile I want the links to scroll down vertically from the top.
On mobile I want theme toggle in the list of links.



Here is the html template I am using:





<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="Malone University - Explore knowledge, courses, and community resources.">
  <title> | Malone University</title>
  <link rel="icon" href="/image/favicon.ico" type="image/x-icon">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/component/css/main.css" />
  </head>
<body>


 <div class="logo-container">
      <a href="/index"><img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Malone University Logo" class="logo-img"></a>
      <span class="school-name">Malone University</span>
    </div> 

  <!-- ===== NAVBAR ===== -->
  <div id="navbar-placeholder"></div>

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <div id="hero-placeholder"></div>

  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>Sample Section</h2>
      <p>This is a placeholder paragraph. <a href="#">Sample Link</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- ===== FOOTER ===== -->
  <div id="footer-placeholder"></div>

  <!-- ===== THEME TOGGLE SCRIPT ===== -->
  <script src="components/script/js/theme-toggle.js"></script>
  <script>


/*  best practice is to wrap in DOMContentLoaded to ensure placeholders exist: */
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {

    // Simple component loader
    async function loadComponent(id, path) {
      const res = await fetch(path);
      const html = await res.text();
      document.getElementById(id).innerHTML = html;
    }


    loadComponent('navbar-placeholder', 'components/navbar.html');
    loadComponent('hero-placeholder', 'components/hero.html');
    loadComponent('footer-placeholder', 'components/footer.html');
    });
  </script>
  
  
  <script src="/component/script/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>



